<h1 id="process-interest" sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="26">Process interest</h1>

[!include[banner](../../includes/banner.md)]
<p sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="30">This procedure shows how to create, print, and post interest notes. This task uses the USMF demo company.</p>
<h2 id="set-up-interest-on-the-posting-profile" sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="33">Set up interest on the posting profile</h2>
<ol sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="34">
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="34">In the <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="34">Navigation pane</strong>, go to <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="34">Modules &gt; Credit and collections &gt; Setup &gt; Customer posting profiles</strong>.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="35">Click <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="35">Edit</strong>.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="36">In the <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="36">Setup fastTab</strong>, in the <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="36">Interest code</strong> field, select an interest code from the drop-down list. If you do not want interest calculated for transactions using this posting profile, leave the field blank. The <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="36">Table restriction</strong> fastTab allows you to change the way that interest is processed. If this field is set to Yes, then interest will be calculated for this posting profile.</li>
</ol>
<h2 id="calculate-interest" sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="38">Calculate interest</h2>
<ol sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="39">
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="39">In the <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="39">Navigation pane</strong>, go to <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="39">Modules &gt; Credit and collections &gt; Interest &gt; Create interest notes</strong>.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="40">You must select the transaction types for which you will calculate interest. All of the open transactions for these types will be included in the calculation.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="41">If you set <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="41">Interest</strong> to 'Yes', you will calculate interest on interest. You may want to check the laws governing the calculation of interest on interest before including these transactions.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="42">In the <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="42">From date</strong> field, enter a date from which the interest will be calculated. If you do not specific a <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="42">From date</strong>, then all unposted interest notes will be canceled and interest will be recalculated from the transaction date.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="43">In the <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="43">To date</strong> field, enter a date to which the interest would be calculated.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="44">In the <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="44">Use posting profile from</strong> field, select an option. There are three posting profile options:
<ul sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="45">
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="45">Account – Use the posting profile that is assigned to the customer account for each interest note.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="46">Select – Use the posting profile that you select in the Posting profile field.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="47">Transaction – Use the individual posting profile from transactions on which interest is calculated for each interest note. Transactions that do not have an assigned posting profile will use the posting profile that is specified in the Ledger and sales tax area of the Accounts receivable parameters form.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="48">Expand the <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="48">Records to include</strong> fastTab.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="49">Click <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="49">Filter</strong>.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="50">In the <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="50">Criteria</strong> field, enter a Customer ID. For example, enter 'US-001'.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="51">Click <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="51">OK</strong>.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="52">Click <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="52">OK</strong>.</li>
</ol>
<h2 id="print-interest-notes" sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="54">Print interest notes</h2>
<ol sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="55">
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="55">In the <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="55">Navigation pane</strong>, go to <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="55">Modules &gt; Credit and collections &gt; Interest &gt; Review and process interest notes</strong>.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="56">In the <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="56">Status</strong> field, select 'Created'.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="57">In the <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="57">Printed</strong> field, select 'Not printed'.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="58">Click <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="58">Print</strong>.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="59">Expand the <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="59">Records to include</strong> fastTab.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="60">Click <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="60">OK</strong>.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="61">Close the page.</li>
</ol>
<h2 id="post-the-interest-note" sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="63">Post the interest note</h2>
<ol sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="64">
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="64">Select an interest note that is ready to post (status is created).</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="65">Click <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="65">Post</strong>.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="66">Enter the posting date for the interest note. Select Yes to create a general ledger transaction for each interest note. If you do not select Yes, the interest on all interest notes to the customer is accumulated and posted to the general ledger in one transaction.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="67">Expand the <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="67">Records to include</strong> fastTab.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="68">Click <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="68">OK</strong>.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="69">In the <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/accounts-receivable/tasks/process-interest.md" sourcestartlinenumber="69">Status</strong> field, select 'Posted'.</li>
</ol>
